{"questionId":"11029","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Physical properties of elements vary according to atomic number. Sections 6 to 9 of the data booklet list some of these properties.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/43377c5a69c579d225b752a8574152b5900dd137.png\" width=\"753\" height=\"519\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Sketch how the first ionization energies of elements vary with their atomic radius.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/51444ffa5a1b17b0e192c3a2f0432f08a8ac88db.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"272\"></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/ef6a16e0babc29cd7358b03439213f4af5a7b64d.png\" width=\"266\" height=\"251\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>[<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">✔</span>]</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Accept any negative sloping line.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Do <strong>not</strong> award mark if line touches either axis.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11029","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ1.1b(iv)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Sketch how the first ionization energies of elements vary with their atomic radius.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b(iv)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Periodicity","3.2 Periodic trends","Core","Topic 3: Periodicity"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}